cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to estimate 3D human pose and shape from 2D images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new architecture that facilitates unsupervised or lightly supervised learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the representation of body parts, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper involves the use of images, which is a common technique in the field of Multimedia (cs.MM).
